data.description:
This Custom Built Luxury home located just outside of Darby, MT sits on Laird Creek and bordered by Forest Service. This offers the perfect retreat for those who love the outdoors but want to enjoy comfortable modern amenities. No detail was spared in building this home.  Large windows and multiple decks were tailored toward the views and creek. Beautiful circle sawn wood flooring creates a warm feel throughout the home. The expansive windows let in the feel of the outdoors. The chef’s kitchen with stainless steel appliances, alder cabinets and granite counter tops allow for plenty of work space and is open to the dining and living spaces. Downstairs you will find a large gathering space along with a custom built wet bar and access to a covered porch.  Along with 2 bedrooms, one with en suite, an office space, a second full bath and plenty of doors to access the exterior. Enjoy the outside with mature landscaping, underground sprinklers, a greenhouse, fenced garden area and plenty of garage and shop space.  Elk and Mule Deer are often grazing just outside..  
There are endless outdoor activities to take advantage of from this property including horse back riding, hiking, ATV, snowmobiling, skiing, fishing and hunting.  Aside from the National Forest access, this home is one mile from the East Fork of the Bitterroot River. Widely considered one of the best fishing rivers in the world. Only 20 minutes from Lost Trail Ski Area and Chief Joseph Pass X-Country Ski Area.
